{
  "date": "2026-03-05",
  "poem": {
    "content": "In rural fields, a student's gaze,\nAcross wide space, a purpose sways.\nA local swing, a blessèd view,\nDuring sunlit hours, skies of blue.\n\nHis method slow, a woolly thought,\nA core of dreams, intensely wrought.\nHe'd join the dance, the wind's soft plea,\nBut shadows gather, silently.\n\nThey suffer, yes, within their space,\nA butter-soft forgiving grace,\nThat cannot mend the heart's deep tear,\nOr quiet down the rising fear.\n\nHe starts to reflect, a silver shine,\nOn futures lost, and paths declined.\nBeneath the stars, a whispered vow,\nTo rise above, somehow, somewhow.\n\nThe rural heart, it knows its pain,\nAnd seeks the light, again, again.",
